00:24:01,860 --> 00:24:04,070
I came across
such a messed-up news article.

265
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:09,780
How dare they, when Mr. Gong Heechul here
is the best social studies instructor.

266
00:24:11,120 --> 00:24:13,580
Jeez, don't you know
they are fishing for some traction?

267
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:14,960
Right?

268
00:24:15,910 --> 00:24:18,380
Those new academies these days

269
00:24:18,460 --> 00:24:22,760
always put my name in
to promote their own instructors.

270
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:27,050
You should be thanking me, sir.
It's free promotion for Gotop, you know?

271
00:24:27,130 --> 00:24:29,640
I can promote the company
just fine on my own.

272
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,510
Besides, money doesn't lie.

273
00:24:33,850 --> 00:24:37,190
If our sales were to drop even a tiny bit,

274
00:24:38,190 --> 00:24:41,570
I'd really like to know
the name of that instructor.

275
00:24:43,530 --> 00:24:44,400
Right.

276
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:48,320
The best instructor is
the one with the highest profits.

277
00:24:49,570 --> 00:24:53,830
Your value today must go up
even by 100 won compared to yesterday,

278
00:24:54,450 --> 00:24:57,330
if you want to survive
here at Gotop Education.

279
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,000
Also…

280
00:25:04,170 --> 00:25:06,050
-Mr. Oh!
-Deputy CEO!

281
00:25:06,130 --> 00:25:07,300
Mr. Oh, you're here.

282
00:25:21,310 --> 00:25:23,320
RECIPIENT: NOH GOJIN

283
00:25:34,790 --> 00:25:36,500
I put a package on your desk.

284
00:25:37,790 --> 00:25:39,620
-Hello.
-Hello.

285
00:25:39,750 --> 00:25:40,580
You know…

286
00:25:48,470 --> 00:25:49,800
Are you going to have some tea?

287
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:52,260
If it's for me, I'm good, sir.

288
00:25:53,430 --> 00:25:55,810
It's just us here. Drop the honorifics.

289
00:25:55,890 --> 00:25:57,470
We're at work, sir.

290
00:25:59,230 --> 00:26:00,140
Enough already.

291
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:06,570
I'll take care of Mr. Kang's dismissal,
so nothing backfires.

292
00:26:07,190 --> 00:26:08,190
Okay.

293
00:26:10,530 --> 00:26:11,860
In that case,

294
00:26:11,950 --> 00:26:13,700
let's grab dinner tonight.

295
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:15,830
I'm sorry, sir.

296
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:18,700
I have an important appointment today.

297
00:26:18,950 --> 00:26:20,040
I apologize.

298
00:26:21,670 --> 00:26:24,040
You have plans today?

299
00:26:24,130 --> 00:26:25,290
Yes.

300
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:28,380
Okay, then.

301
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:31,680
-You may go now.
-Okay. Thank you.

302
00:26:39,220 --> 00:26:40,230
He has plans?

303
00:26:41,190 --> 00:26:42,810
He forgot about my birthday?

304
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:47,110
Goddamn birthday.

305
00:26:48,150 --> 00:26:50,570
Who cares about birthdays anyway?

306
00:26:51,070 --> 00:26:52,860
The most childish thing in the world

307
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:56,370
is blowing out candles on birthdays
and making a huge scene out of it.

308
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,080
Ta-da!

309
00:27:06,500 --> 00:27:08,920
Happy birthday to you

310
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:13,630
Happy birthday, my dear brother Gojin
Happy birthday to you

311
00:27:14,090 --> 00:27:16,010
Gojin, happy birthday.

312
00:27:25,230 --> 00:27:26,560
What is this? How childish.

313
00:27:26,650 --> 00:27:30,320
Gojin, I'm really sorry
that I can't have dinner with you today.

314
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:32,360
I know it's just you.

315
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:36,870
Birthdays are overrated.

316
00:27:37,870 --> 00:27:39,740
Gosh, I don't even like cake.

317
00:27:39,830 --> 00:27:41,410
Come on. Have some.

318
00:27:45,250 --> 00:27:46,330
No peaches in it, right?

319
00:27:46,420 --> 00:27:50,050
Who else but me would know
that you're allergic to peaches?

320
00:27:50,130 --> 00:27:52,590
Of course not. Don't worry and eat.

321
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:57,720
Does it taste good?

322
00:27:58,760 --> 00:27:59,720
Not bad.

323
00:28:04,270 --> 00:28:07,230
Gojin, can you give Mr. Kang

324
00:28:07,810 --> 00:28:09,400
another chance?

325
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:11,150
I thought you would take care of it.

326
00:28:11,230 --> 00:28:14,650
That was the deputy CEO
of Gotop Education speaking.

327
00:28:14,740 --> 00:28:19,870
But I'm asking you now…
as your one and only brother.

328
00:28:22,870 --> 00:28:24,790
I don't have to tell you

329
00:28:25,410 --> 00:28:26,830
how important you are to me. Right?

330
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:30,880
Without you, there would be
no Gotop Education or me.

331
00:28:31,460 --> 00:28:36,340
So I take your word for it
when it comes to most things. However…

332
00:28:37,510 --> 00:28:38,800
not Kang Min.

333
00:28:40,180 --> 00:28:42,180
That punk has already crossed the line.

334
00:28:52,690 --> 00:28:56,280
Oh, right. Are you really going
to do the special lecture?

335
00:28:56,780 --> 00:28:59,620
To be honest, I'm against it.

336
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:02,580
You'll be doing it with Mr. Park
who ruined your life.

337
00:29:04,040 --> 00:29:06,620
That's why I'm doing it,
so I can see that jerk's face.

338
00:29:08,870 --> 00:29:10,460
GOTOP EDUCATION CEO NOH GOJIN

339
00:29:23,560 --> 00:29:24,560
What is it?

340
00:29:25,390 --> 00:29:26,390
What?

341
00:29:28,440 --> 00:29:31,020
It's nothing. It's something I ordered.

342
00:29:33,770 --> 00:29:35,780
When did you say
you were going to the States?

343
00:29:37,070 --> 00:29:40,110
On the 24th. I'll be gone for five days.

344
00:29:40,780 --> 00:29:42,910
-That's pretty long.
-Gosh, tell me about it.

345
00:29:42,990 --> 00:29:45,830
I'll be having three meetings
with Mos Company.

346
00:29:46,750 --> 00:29:48,620
This is our first step
into the American market.

347
00:29:48,710 --> 00:29:49,870
We ought to be careful.

348
00:29:50,500 --> 00:29:53,500
Oh, right. And Eutteum School was
acquired by Gunil Group.

349
00:29:53,590 --> 00:29:54,880
Darn it.

350
00:29:55,710 --> 00:29:57,970
Why are the conglomerates
getting into our industry?

351
00:29:58,050 --> 00:30:00,680
What do you plan to do on your vacation?
Going to Gangneung again?

352
00:30:01,510 --> 00:30:04,470
Don't just stay in your vacation house
and get around.

353
00:30:04,550 --> 00:30:06,720
The beaches in Gangneung
are really nice, you know.

354
00:30:08,230 --> 00:30:09,730
Don't worry about me.

355
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:12,310
I'll be spending
a romantic time with my girlfriend.

356
00:30:12,900 --> 00:30:14,560
-You don't have a girlfriend.
-I do.

357
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:16,900
I'll go right after the special lecture

358
00:30:16,980 --> 00:30:19,490
and spend an amazing time
with my girlfriend. So don't you dare

359
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:21,910
call me from the States.

360
00:30:21,990 --> 00:30:24,160
Yes, sir. I won't.

361
00:30:25,870 --> 00:30:28,290
I can't believe I'm using
last year's summer vacation days now.

362
00:30:28,370 --> 00:30:30,620
But can you reconsider
the special lecture--

363
00:30:30,710 --> 00:30:32,370
Gosh, seriously. There you go again.

364
00:30:32,460 --> 00:30:35,250
Stop that nonsense
and just get back to work.

365
00:30:39,670 --> 00:30:40,630
Oh, Gojin.

366
00:30:41,930 --> 00:30:43,640
Happy birthday.

367
00:31:49,870 --> 00:31:50,910
WRITING THIS WITH MY BLOOD NOW
YOUR BLOOD NEXT TIME

368
00:31:50,990 --> 00:31:52,290
YOU SCUMBAG!
YOU MAKE ME WANT TO VOMIT

369
00:31:52,370 --> 00:31:55,080
NOH GOJIN, I HOPE YOU DIE

370
00:31:57,420 --> 00:31:59,000
It's obvious

371
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:03,380
that this punk has no life.

372
00:32:15,350 --> 00:32:16,600
How cute.

373
00:32:26,910 --> 00:32:28,450
Here is your sandwich, ma'am.

374
00:32:33,250 --> 00:32:34,080
What?

375
00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:37,370
This is ham and cheese.

376
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:39,460
Where's the beef special?

377
00:32:41,130 --> 00:32:42,960
Well, it was sold out.

378
00:32:43,630 --> 00:32:45,760
I'll go earlier next time. I'm sorry.

379
00:32:46,340 --> 00:32:48,140
I see. There is no need for that.

380
00:32:49,510 --> 00:32:51,560
Next time, just quit.

381
00:32:52,560 --> 00:32:56,270
The fact that you stayed
this long assisting our CEO

382
00:32:57,020 --> 00:32:58,020
is a tragedy.

383
00:32:58,810 --> 00:32:59,940
A tragedy.

384
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:11,370
You eat it.

385
00:34:00,710 --> 00:34:02,960
1 YEAR!

386
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:36,330
Pack your things.

387
00:34:50,720 --> 00:34:53,390
If this is all you can do, just quit!

388
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:09,400
Run now. This is hell.

389
00:35:09,780 --> 00:35:11,900
Not even Hades would put up with this!

390
00:35:22,250 --> 00:35:23,420
No.

391
00:35:24,330 --> 00:35:25,670
I put up with it.

392
00:35:26,540 --> 00:35:28,500
I gave it my all and put up with it.

393
00:35:28,590 --> 00:35:31,300
1 YEAR!

394
00:35:31,970 --> 00:35:34,220
I put up with it for a year.

395
00:35:37,970 --> 00:35:39,470
I'm so proud of you, Lee Sina!

396
00:36:05,790 --> 00:36:07,170
Happy birthday indeed.

397
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,090
What are you doing over there?

398
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:19,890
-Hurry. Come on.
-Let's run.

399
00:36:19,970 --> 00:36:21,310
-Darn it.
-Hurry.

400
00:36:21,390 --> 00:36:22,930
-One, two, three.
-One, two, three.

401
00:36:24,100 --> 00:36:25,690
-Come on. Let's go.
-There.

402
00:36:25,770 --> 00:36:26,770
-Hurry.
-No, that way.

403
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:38,820
My condolences.

404
00:36:55,670 --> 00:36:56,880
Mr. Oh.

405
00:36:56,970 --> 00:36:58,550
Are you going home now?

406
00:36:58,640 --> 00:36:59,510
Yes.

407
00:37:00,100 --> 00:37:01,100
Ms. Lee,

408
00:37:02,470 --> 00:37:04,350
can we talk for a moment?

409
00:37:05,180 --> 00:37:07,770
Well… Okay.

410
00:37:09,230 --> 00:37:12,900
Ta-da! Ms. Lee, congratulations
on your one-year work anniversary!

411
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:16,070
How… did you know?

412
00:37:16,690 --> 00:37:18,700
Mr. Noh asked me to give this to you.

413
00:37:22,990 --> 00:37:24,330
I'm sure he knows too.

414
00:37:24,910 --> 00:37:26,960
Thank you so much for your hard work.

415
00:37:28,210 --> 00:37:29,420
Thank you.

416
00:37:30,380 --> 00:37:31,380
And this.

417
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:35,340
A small bonus for your vacation funds.

418
00:37:36,970 --> 00:37:37,880
Vacation funds?

419
00:37:37,970 --> 00:37:41,180
You should take some days off
while Mr. Noh is on vacation, Ms. Lee.

420
00:37:41,260 --> 00:37:43,390
You didn't get off
summer vacation last year either.

421
00:37:44,430 --> 00:37:45,270
Well…

422
00:37:48,520 --> 00:37:49,600
Thank you.

423
00:37:51,020 --> 00:37:53,980
Also… don't give up on your dream

424
00:37:54,770 --> 00:37:56,400
of becoming an instructor.

425
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:58,990
Wherever you are

426
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:00,490
or whatever you may be doing,

427
00:38:00,570 --> 00:38:03,030
as long as
you don't give up on your dream,

428
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:06,290
your dream will come true in the end.

429
00:38:07,290 --> 00:38:09,290
I'll let you know if there's an opening.

430
00:38:10,250 --> 00:38:12,330
Okay. Thank you.

431
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:15,630
This is going to taste great

432
00:38:16,300 --> 00:38:17,300
Let's eat.

433
00:38:25,260 --> 00:38:26,260
What's that?

434
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:36,860
Why did you buy flowers?

435
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:38,860
I didn't. They were a gift.

436
00:38:38,940 --> 00:38:39,860
From whom?

437
00:38:40,530 --> 00:38:41,740
My angel.

438
00:38:42,610 --> 00:38:44,030
"My angel"?

439
00:38:45,330 --> 00:38:47,120
Your crush, the deputy CEO?
Did he ask you out?

440
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:48,700
No, it's not like that.

441
00:38:49,500 --> 00:38:52,330
Then why are you blushing?

442
00:38:53,210 --> 00:38:54,580
I'm not blushing.

443
00:38:54,670 --> 00:38:57,000
If he didn't ask you out,
why did he give you flowers?

444
00:38:58,090 --> 00:38:59,550
For my one-year work anniversary.

445
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,050
He thanked me for my work.

446
00:39:01,130 --> 00:39:02,880
Jeez, that's all?

447
00:39:05,350 --> 00:39:07,510
Okhee, it's finally been a year for me.

448
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:09,810
I put up working
as Mr. Noh Manners' secretary for a year!

449
00:39:09,890 --> 00:39:11,850
I'll have a chance to apply
if there's an opening!

450
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:14,100
My dad was right.

451
00:39:14,190 --> 00:39:15,650
"Good things come to those who wait."

452
00:39:15,730 --> 00:39:18,860
Hey. Wait another year
and you'll become a druggie.

453
00:39:18,940 --> 00:39:20,400
Go get a head CT.

454
00:39:20,490 --> 00:39:22,200
You've been
constantly taking headache pills.

455
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:23,820
Gosh, you nag so much.

456
00:39:24,410 --> 00:39:25,870
I already booked an appointment.

457
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:30,500
He really is an angel without wings.

458
00:39:30,580 --> 00:39:32,960
How did he even remember this?

459
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:34,210
All of his secretaries quit.

460
00:39:34,870 --> 00:39:37,000
No one has lasted three months
under that jerk,

461
00:39:37,090 --> 00:39:38,550
but you lasted a year.

462
00:39:38,630 --> 00:39:42,130
He must be so grateful
to have a pushover like you.

463
00:39:43,050 --> 00:39:44,590
But he's terrible at giving gifts.

464
00:39:44,880 --> 00:39:46,970
You're losing hair
and suffering from shingles,

465
00:39:47,050 --> 00:39:48,760
chronic migraines, and indigestion.

466
00:39:48,850 --> 00:39:50,850
You had to take a fistful of pills.

467
00:39:51,310 --> 00:39:54,640
Flowers? He should've bought you
some ribeye steak.

468
00:39:56,190 --> 00:39:58,690
-You get out.
-Jeez, I just meant…

469
00:39:58,770 --> 00:40:00,690
-Get out.
-Don't push. It's dangerous. Gosh!

470
00:40:14,290 --> 00:40:16,620
“Don't give up on your dream
of becoming an instructor.”

471
00:40:18,250 --> 00:40:20,670
Gosh, he's so cool.

472
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:28,890
MR. NOH GOJIN, MR. PARK YANGTAE
ROOTING FOR THE NEXT GENERATION

473
00:40:47,450 --> 00:40:49,740
It's been a while
since I've been back to my alma mater.

474
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:55,370
-Hello.
-Hello. Welcome.

475
00:40:55,460 --> 00:40:56,290
It's been so long.

476
00:40:57,830 --> 00:41:00,040
-Thank you for inviting me.
-Welcome.

477
00:41:00,130 --> 00:41:01,590
Nice to meet you.

478
00:41:03,550 --> 00:41:04,760
Is that…

479
00:41:29,990 --> 00:41:30,990
Welcome.

480
00:41:33,370 --> 00:41:35,910
The two best instructors
from the private education sector,

481
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:38,330
Mr. Noh Gojin of Gotop Education

482
00:41:38,410 --> 00:41:40,420
and Mr. Park Yangtae of Ilpum Edu.

483
00:41:40,500 --> 00:41:42,590
I'm so happy to have you both here.

484
00:41:43,040 --> 00:41:44,340
The two best instructors?

485
00:41:47,300 --> 00:41:49,510
You're going to give people
the wrong idea.

486
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:52,600
Ilpum Edu has
a long history and tradition.

487
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:54,930
How could it be compared
to Gotop with no roots?

488
00:41:55,260 --> 00:41:56,850
You sure are funny.

489
00:41:58,180 --> 00:41:59,810
Shall we go inside?

490
00:42:01,900 --> 00:42:03,230
What's wrong?

491
00:42:04,070 --> 00:42:05,820
Number one…

492
00:42:07,740 --> 00:42:10,320
shouldn't walk side by side
with lowly number two.

493
00:42:25,630 --> 00:42:27,130
He's so annoying.

494
00:42:27,210 --> 00:42:29,340
You think you're a movie star? Jeez.

495
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:37,890
What a great world we live in now.

496
00:42:38,270 --> 00:42:40,940
How did a lowlife janitor
without any class

497
00:42:41,140 --> 00:42:44,730
get to give a lecture
at the most prestigious university?

498
00:42:49,240 --> 00:42:50,650
Don't you agree, Mr. Noh?

499
00:43:22,020 --> 00:43:25,020
CEO PARK YANGTAE

