00:45:55,760 --> 00:45:56,760
-Why you--
-Oh, right.

528
00:45:57,510 --> 00:46:00,680
Don't go on the Internet today.

529
00:46:01,390 --> 00:46:03,010
You'll be too embarrassed to fall asleep.

530
00:46:03,510 --> 00:46:04,680
Why you…

531
00:46:05,510 --> 00:46:06,390
Hey!

532
00:46:06,970 --> 00:46:08,980
Hey, Noh Gojin! Stop right there!

533
00:46:09,560 --> 00:46:10,480
Hey!

534
00:46:17,320 --> 00:46:18,990
Who are these two-bit thugs?

535
00:46:19,650 --> 00:46:21,030
Do you have a death wish?

536
00:46:21,660 --> 00:46:24,990
Darn you, Noh Gojin!
I'm going to kill you!

537
00:46:25,080 --> 00:46:26,910
-Sir, please calm down.
-Noh Gojin! Hey!

538
00:46:26,990 --> 00:46:28,410
Darn it. Let go of me!

539
00:46:32,040 --> 00:46:34,880
NOH GOJIN, THE STAR LECTURER!
ROOTING FOR THE NEXT GENERATION

540
00:46:34,960 --> 00:46:38,010
MR. NOH GOJIN, MR. PARK YANGTAE
SPECIAL GUEST LECTURE

541
00:46:40,340 --> 00:46:41,930
CEO NOH GOJIN

542
00:46:44,970 --> 00:46:46,060
Move aside.

543
00:46:49,890 --> 00:46:52,600
Hey, where's the file for the big data?

544
00:46:52,690 --> 00:46:56,360
You said you would bring it
after you check it yesterday.

545
00:46:59,320 --> 00:47:00,150
Where did I put it?

546
00:47:01,570 --> 00:47:03,490
Where is it? Where did I put it?

547
00:47:03,570 --> 00:47:04,410
Oh, no! This is bad.

548
00:47:05,070 --> 00:47:07,120
If you were the file, where would you be?

549
00:47:07,200 --> 00:47:09,040
What? You said you would--

550
00:47:09,120 --> 00:47:12,420
Forget it.
Mr. Noh is going to throw a fit.

551
00:47:12,500 --> 00:47:14,170
I'm in trouble. What do I do?

552
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:22,090
Tell Ms. Lee to bring it.

553
00:47:22,170 --> 00:47:23,720
But you don't know where it is.

554
00:47:23,800 --> 00:47:26,680
Right. So tell Ms. Lee
to find it and bring it here.

555
00:47:27,680 --> 00:47:28,510
As mentioned,

556
00:47:28,640 --> 00:47:31,980
very special guests
have come to our school today.

557
00:47:32,560 --> 00:47:34,020
Mr. Park Yangtae of Ilpum Edu

558
00:47:34,100 --> 00:47:36,150
who represents
the private education sector

559
00:47:36,230 --> 00:47:40,030
and the star instructor,
Mr. Noh Gojin of Gotop Education.

560
00:47:40,110 --> 00:47:41,360
Let's give them a warm welcome.

561
00:47:41,440 --> 00:47:46,240
MR. NOH GOJIN, MR. PARK YANGTAE
SPECIAL GUEST LECTURE

562
00:47:54,540 --> 00:47:56,960
After listening
to their lectures for the youth,

563
00:47:57,040 --> 00:48:00,340
we'll also have a Q and A session.

564
00:48:00,420 --> 00:48:05,260
First, Mr. Park Yangtae
of Ilpum Edu will give his lecture.

565
00:48:13,810 --> 00:48:17,520
Hello, I'm Park Yangtae,
the CEO of Ilpum Edu.

566
00:48:17,610 --> 00:48:20,610
I feel so great and youthful again

567
00:48:21,030 --> 00:48:24,070
standing here looking at you today.

568
00:48:24,900 --> 00:48:29,200
I'm nervous and full of emotions
to be back at my alma mater

569
00:48:29,830 --> 00:48:31,450
after so long…

570
00:48:34,040 --> 00:48:35,330
My apologies.

571
00:48:36,670 --> 00:48:37,500
Mr. Park.

572
00:48:42,210 --> 00:48:43,050
I'm good.

573
00:48:43,630 --> 00:48:44,630
Come on, Mr. Park.

574
00:48:45,050 --> 00:48:46,590
Are you still upset?

575
00:48:54,730 --> 00:48:55,560
Everyone,

576
00:48:56,690 --> 00:48:58,440
earlier in the waiting room,

577
00:48:59,110 --> 00:49:00,940
I pulled a small prank on Mr. Park.

578
00:49:02,230 --> 00:49:04,610
My intention was
to get friendlier with Mr. Park,

579
00:49:04,690 --> 00:49:07,740
but he seems to have been upset about it.

580
00:49:09,700 --> 00:49:12,450
Mr. Park, I would like to apologize.

581
00:49:12,950 --> 00:49:15,080
Please accept this water
as a token of my apology

582
00:49:16,120 --> 00:49:17,370
and forgive me.

583
00:49:32,600 --> 00:49:36,020
Did you spike it
with the strongest you could find?

584
00:49:36,100 --> 00:49:36,980
Yes, sir.

585
00:49:47,150 --> 00:49:49,320
Please drink up!

586
00:49:55,370 --> 00:49:56,580
One more thing, everyone.

587
00:49:57,790 --> 00:50:01,670
Please give a big round of applause
to Mr. Park once again.

588
00:50:01,750 --> 00:50:02,670
Mr. Park…

589
00:50:04,630 --> 00:50:06,170
will donate one billion won

590
00:50:07,630 --> 00:50:09,800
to his alma mater for you guys!

591
00:50:09,880 --> 00:50:11,760
One billion won?

592
00:50:14,010 --> 00:50:15,560
THE LEGEND OF ADMISSIONS
CEO PARK YANGTAE

593
00:50:16,970 --> 00:50:20,730
Gosh, he loves his juniors so much.

594
00:50:20,810 --> 00:50:22,690
I'm so touched.

595
00:50:25,150 --> 00:50:26,150
All right now,

596
00:50:26,230 --> 00:50:31,030
why don't we listen
to the great Mr. Park's lecture now?

597
00:50:32,820 --> 00:50:33,780
Sir,

598
00:50:34,910 --> 00:50:37,040
you have my full attention.

599
00:50:47,460 --> 00:50:49,840
It only feels like yesterday

600
00:50:50,550 --> 00:50:53,640
I was sitting where you are sitting now.

601
00:50:55,430 --> 00:50:58,600
I'm feeling so many things right now.

602
00:51:04,190 --> 00:51:05,190
Today…

603
00:51:08,400 --> 00:51:09,690
-Today…
-What's going on?

604
00:51:11,070 --> 00:51:14,950
I'll be talking about the path
that the youth ought to take and…

605
00:51:19,620 --> 00:51:22,000
the world of online classes…

606
00:51:25,580 --> 00:51:27,380
you are curious about…

607
00:51:31,170 --> 00:51:32,590
-Please excuse me.
-What?

608
00:51:32,680 --> 00:51:34,800
-One moment.
-What's wrong with him?

609
00:51:39,720 --> 00:51:43,850
Mr. Park must be feeling
a bit too nervous.

610
00:51:44,810 --> 00:51:47,900
Perhaps… why don't I start then?

611
00:51:57,570 --> 00:51:58,580
Oh, gosh.

612
00:51:59,620 --> 00:52:01,660
Excuse me. Help!

613
00:52:01,750 --> 00:52:03,120
It's urgent! Please!

614
00:52:26,770 --> 00:52:28,020
Gosh.

615
00:52:52,090 --> 00:52:53,090
Questions?

616
00:52:57,510 --> 00:52:58,680
Any questions?

617
00:53:03,140 --> 00:53:06,480
You with the glasses in the sixth row.

618
00:53:08,440 --> 00:53:10,860
Is your IQ really 190?

619
00:53:12,150 --> 00:53:16,030
I entered the Mega Society 14 years ago.

620
00:53:16,740 --> 00:53:18,280
So it should be higher by now.

621
00:53:19,570 --> 00:53:20,700
Next question.

622
00:53:23,740 --> 00:53:26,410
Aren't you sick of teaching
the same CSAT Math every year?

623
00:53:26,500 --> 00:53:28,670
I'm very sick of it.

624
00:53:28,750 --> 00:53:29,710
And it's quite lame too.

625
00:53:30,460 --> 00:53:32,750
-Then why do you do it?
-To make money.

626
00:53:35,760 --> 00:53:38,010
What? Is that funny?

627
00:53:38,090 --> 00:53:40,220
Yes, it's a bit disappointing.

628
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:42,890
-Why is that?
-You're a genius.

629
00:53:42,970 --> 00:53:44,930
But you're doing it just for money.

630
00:53:52,230 --> 00:53:53,400
Have you ever…

631
00:53:53,980 --> 00:53:55,980
starved because you had no money?

632
00:53:57,030 --> 00:53:59,070
-No.
-I have. I starved for a week

633
00:53:59,150 --> 00:54:00,820
because I didn't have any money.

634
00:54:03,080 --> 00:54:06,450
My parents killed themselves
because they were poor.

635
00:54:06,540 --> 00:54:08,540
My grandma also died in pain

636
00:54:09,920 --> 00:54:13,500
because she couldn't afford
to get her cancer treated in time.

637
00:54:13,590 --> 00:54:15,250
And I, who was nine at the time…

638
00:54:17,670 --> 00:54:19,470
could only watch her suffer and die.

639
00:54:24,970 --> 00:54:27,390
I'm going to do
everything I can to make money.

640
00:54:28,020 --> 00:54:32,480
I won't die doing manual labor
like William James Sidis

641
00:54:32,560 --> 00:54:35,860
or of tuberculosis
like Srinivasa Ramanujan.

642
00:54:36,360 --> 00:54:37,530
I…

643
00:54:39,610 --> 00:54:42,360
do not want to die
a miserable death because of poverty.

644
00:54:47,910 --> 00:54:49,120
ROOTING FOR THE NEXT GENERATION

645
00:54:56,170 --> 00:54:59,470
My story was a bit somber, wasn't it?

646
00:55:00,970 --> 00:55:03,640
But don't you feel

647
00:55:03,970 --> 00:55:05,930
like we've become a bit closer now?

648
00:55:08,810 --> 00:55:13,600
Yes. Giving a lecture wouldn't be any fun
without these gleaming eyes.

649
00:55:14,980 --> 00:55:19,360
All right.
Let me start my real lecture now.

650
00:55:20,150 --> 00:55:21,320
Please look over here.

651
00:55:21,400 --> 00:55:24,530
SPECIAL GUEST LECTURE

652
00:55:32,790 --> 00:55:34,790
Ms. Lee forgot the flash drive.

653
00:55:34,880 --> 00:55:37,500
I'm sorry. I should've prepared it myself.

654
00:55:37,750 --> 00:55:39,090
It's my fault.

655
00:55:45,680 --> 00:55:46,970
Well…

656
00:55:48,600 --> 00:55:50,310
My secretary forgot

657
00:55:51,430 --> 00:55:52,770
the presentation…

658
00:56:06,820 --> 00:56:07,780
Wait.

659
00:56:12,830 --> 00:56:13,870
Does anyone here

660
00:56:14,920 --> 00:56:16,710
want to be an instructor?

661
00:56:20,800 --> 00:56:21,920
That's a lot of you.

662
00:56:23,170 --> 00:56:26,430
But if you are one of these people,

663
00:56:27,510 --> 00:56:30,680
you should give up that dream
right away. Because…

664
00:56:31,600 --> 00:56:34,640
you'll never become an instructor.

665
00:56:36,020 --> 00:56:38,230
Curious to find out who?

666
00:56:59,040 --> 00:57:01,300
If you can't help prepare for others,

667
00:57:01,380 --> 00:57:03,960
you can't help prepare
for yourself either. Why?

668
00:57:05,260 --> 00:57:07,340
People like that

669
00:57:07,970 --> 00:57:11,310
are mostly careless,
irresponsible, and lazy.

670
00:57:12,850 --> 00:57:16,140
In the ever-changing battlefield
of the online education industry,

671
00:57:18,350 --> 00:57:19,270
they will…

672
00:57:22,230 --> 00:57:24,740
never become an instructor.

673
00:57:27,530 --> 00:57:28,910
Or else, I'll eat my hat.

674
00:57:48,720 --> 00:57:51,720
NOH GOJIN'S MATHEMATICAL CONCEPTS

675
00:58:22,790 --> 00:58:24,250
Gosh, my head hurts.

676
00:58:51,410 --> 00:58:52,490
They will…

677
00:58:54,700 --> 00:58:57,200
never become an instructor.

678
00:59:10,970 --> 00:59:13,890
Don't give up on your dream
of becoming an instructor.

679
00:59:16,050 --> 00:59:18,850
That's right. Don't give up, Lee Sina.

680
00:59:18,930 --> 00:59:20,310
Don't you know who you are?

681
00:59:20,390 --> 00:59:23,150
You're the miraculous secretary
who survived a year in this hell.

682
00:59:23,520 --> 00:59:25,400
Be confident. That's right.

683
00:59:25,480 --> 00:59:26,570
You can do it, Lee Sina!

684
00:59:29,480 --> 00:59:32,360
Hello! This is Lee Sina from Catch Korean!

685
00:59:32,450 --> 00:59:34,990
Today, we're going to study morphemes,

686
00:59:35,070 --> 00:59:36,780
which a lot of you have
a hard time understanding…

687
00:59:36,870 --> 00:59:37,780
Ms. Lee.

688
00:59:38,410 --> 00:59:39,870
Are you working late today?

689
00:59:39,950 --> 00:59:41,960
Yes, I am!

690
00:59:58,390 --> 01:00:00,180
Ms. Lee Sina, this is Gwangae Hospital.

691
01:00:00,720 --> 01:00:02,600
Your appointment is at 9 a.m. tomorrow.

692
01:00:09,690 --> 01:00:10,570
Ms. Lee Sina.

693
01:00:12,070 --> 01:00:13,860
-Yes.
-Please go in.

694
01:00:59,490 --> 01:01:01,490
NOH GOJIN'S MATHEMATICAL CONCEPTS

695
01:01:44,290 --> 01:01:46,710
Pardon me.
Where are all the teaching assistants?

696
01:01:48,330 --> 01:01:50,380
They're having a meeting in Gangneung.

697
01:01:50,460 --> 01:01:52,130
-Gangneung?
-Yeah.

698
01:01:52,210 --> 01:01:55,420
Out of the blue, Mr. Noh made everyone
come to Gangneung this morning.

699
01:01:55,510 --> 01:01:58,050
They were all scrambling
to get over there.

700
01:01:58,130 --> 01:01:59,130
You didn't know?

701
01:01:59,840 --> 01:02:02,140
-No.
-My goodness.

702
01:02:02,220 --> 01:02:04,140
Even I knew it
and I'm just a cleaner here.

703
01:02:04,220 --> 01:02:06,520
How could his secretary not know that?

704
01:02:06,600 --> 01:02:08,640
Jeez, seriously.

705
01:02:41,550 --> 01:02:42,680
Yes? Hello?

706
01:02:43,800 --> 01:02:44,890
Is this Ms. Lee Sina?

707
01:02:45,310 --> 01:02:46,510
Yes, this is she.

708
01:02:46,850 --> 01:02:48,520
I'm calling from Gwangae Hospital.

709
01:02:48,640 --> 01:02:51,140
You were busy earlier,
so you only took the MRI scan, correct?

710
01:02:52,310 --> 01:02:53,310
Yes.

711
01:02:54,020 --> 01:02:55,940
Can you come to the hospital now?

712
01:03:02,990 --> 01:03:05,200
When did your migraines
start to get serious?

713
01:03:07,370 --> 01:03:10,000
I think it's been about a year.

714
01:03:10,080 --> 01:03:12,120
Recently, I've been taking
headache pills every day.

715
01:03:12,210 --> 01:03:13,630
DR. HAN JIHO

716
01:03:16,460 --> 01:03:18,590
I advise you to get admitted.

717
01:03:20,670 --> 01:03:21,720
Get admitted?

718
01:03:21,800 --> 01:03:23,970
Ms. Lee, you have a glioblastoma.

719
01:03:25,180 --> 01:03:27,760
A glio… What's that?

720
01:03:28,470 --> 01:03:30,430
It's cancer. A brain tumor.

721
01:03:31,890 --> 01:03:34,940
You should prepare yourself.

722
01:03:35,730 --> 01:03:38,570
What do you mean, prepare myself?

723
01:03:45,200 --> 01:03:46,370
You're at the final stage.

724
01:03:49,290 --> 01:03:52,330
I… have a brain tumor?

725
01:03:54,790 --> 01:03:56,750
I'm going to die?

726
01:04:09,850 --> 01:04:11,100
Is this a dream?

727
01:04:13,310 --> 01:04:15,810
Am I having a dream right now?

728
01:05:00,980 --> 01:05:04,360
-Did you wait long?
-You didn't have to come.

729
01:05:06,240 --> 01:05:08,410
-Goodness.
-Since it's snowing a lot.

730
01:05:15,620 --> 01:05:17,000
I guess…

731
01:05:18,830 --> 01:05:21,420
I won't be able to get old like them.

732
01:07:22,790 --> 01:07:23,790
Who are you?

733
01:07:28,920 --> 01:07:30,220
I said, who are you?

734
01:07:58,450 --> 01:07:59,330
What's this about?

735
01:08:02,000 --> 01:08:03,540
What the heck are you doing?

736
01:08:09,340 --> 01:08:11,510
How did you get in here?

737
